description:
Frank Turner plays a solo acoustic version of "Girl From The Record Shop"
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube  

Frank Turner released his tenth studio album, 'Undefeated,' on May 3, 2024, but just a couple weeks earlier — on Record Store Day, specifically — Turner found himself in the Twin Cities where he worked a shift and played a show at the Electric Fetus in Minneapolis, where he played a number of songs from the then-forthcoming record. How apropos, then, that one of the songs on the new album is this one, "Girl From The Record Shop."

Credits
Guest – @FrankTurner 
Host – Mac Wilson
Producer – Derrick Stevens

description:
Sierra Ferrell performs "American Dreaming" live in studio
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube

During a tour stop in the Twin Cities to play a show at First Avenue in Minneapolis, Sierra Ferrell and her band visited The Current for a studio session hosted by Jessica Paxton. Watch and listen to a performance of "American Dreaming" above.

Musicians
Sierra Ferrell – vocals, fiddle, guitar

Geoffrey Saunders – bass, backing vocals
Oliver Bates Craven – guitars, fiddle, backing vocals
